 The team will compete at the Commonwealth Games in Birmingham at the end of July and will host the Sevens World Cup at the Cape Town Stadium in September. eNCA’s Justin Ford has more. #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - The high-flying Springbok Sevens teams can look forward to a full programme in 2022. In addition to the regular season, the team will also take part in the Commonwealth Games and the World Cup here on home soil. But there’s also a small matter of their long-serving coach leaving for greener pastures. Meanwhile, Springbok Sevens captain Siviwe Soyizwapi is on the mend after an injury in Spain. * eNCA’s Justin Ford reports.